      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "The largest heating change for any column is actually 11 mW kg Ϫ1 , for a column with 90% cloud cover at 85 mb, but effectively zero cloud water content. The average heating increase is 1 mW kg Ϫ1 due to columns without tropopause cirrus and columns with thick cloud below. Both the heating rates and temperature change are comparable to those obtained by [CITATION_1] for subvisible cirrus in a two-dimensional model."
